    "file": "frontend/src/pages/Profile.tsx",
    "line": 62,
    "summary": "Same hardcoded 'OIDC (SSO)' wrongness as Settings.tsx: in dev-bypass mode the Profile page (which renders the fixed DEV_USER, so it is reachable) claims OIDC SSO authentication.",
    "failure_scenario": "With `DATAQ_AUTH_MODE=bypass` the auth gate renders the fixed dev user (`DEV_USER` in frontend/src/auth/config.ts) and Profile displays 'Authentication: OIDC (SSO)' for a session that involved no identity provider. If a fix is applied to Settings.tsx per the companion finding, this second copy of the literal must change in lockstep or the two pages drift — the duplication across two pages is itself the maintenance hazard (this PR had to patch the same stale string in two places, and a future auth change repeats that)."
  }
]

